The paper focuses on analyzing the usage and propagation of hashtags in a location-based social media app, which falls under the categories of social networks (cs.SOC) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The study also involves analyzing the content of the posts, which could fall under computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper discusses the design and functionality of the app, which could fall under cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). Finally, the paper uses established metrics for Twitter hashtags, which could also fall under the category of social networks (cs.SOC).
